77
00:03:17,692 --> 00:03:22,834
So when I start animating a new game character, the first thing I start with isn't a run,

78
00:03:22,834 --> 00:03:24,955
an attack, or a jump, or anything like that.

79
00:03:24,955 --> 00:03:26,835
It's the idle pose.

80
00:03:26,835 --> 00:03:28,556
This is the root of all your animations.

81
00:03:28,556 --> 00:03:30,316
This is where they start and end.

82
00:03:31,177 --> 00:03:32,958
What should your idol pose look like though?

83
00:03:32,958 --> 00:03:35,881
You can use the opportunity to get some personality in there,

84
00:03:35,881 --> 00:03:40,025
but also you should keep in mind how the idol will connect to the rest of the character's animations.

85
00:03:40,025 --> 00:03:43,468
For example, for our archer Zebe here,

86
00:03:43,468 --> 00:03:47,591
we needed to make sure his moves matched the way he was holding the bow and arrow in his idol.

87
00:03:47,591 --> 00:03:51,134
A lot of the concepts had him switching hands, so we needed to make sure they all lined up.

88
00:03:51,134 --> 00:03:51,435
Did it switch? Okay.

89
00:03:55,430 --> 00:04:00,075
Also important is to remember not just the idle animation itself, but the transition

90
00:04:00,075 --> 00:04:01,896
to and from your idles.

91
00:04:01,896 --> 00:04:05,460
Game animations are actually interrupting each other all the time because different

92
00:04:05,460 --> 00:04:09,704
things are happening, so making sure that you return to that same base is going to help

93
00:04:09,704 --> 00:04:12,466
your animation feel more seamless as they transition.

94
00:04:14,425 --> 00:04:16,886
And especially in 2D, it's important to remember

95
00:04:16,886 --> 00:04:18,707
that the idol itself is also a motion.

96
00:04:18,707 --> 00:04:20,868
I think what can end up happening

97
00:04:20,868 --> 00:04:23,409
if you don't pay attention is that you treat the idol

98
00:04:23,409 --> 00:04:25,630
as a single pose and animate as if you're easing

99
00:04:25,630 --> 00:04:27,231
into that single pose.

100
00:04:27,231 --> 00:04:29,171
But since the idol itself is a motion,

101
00:04:29,171 --> 00:04:31,132
you need to treat the start and ends

102
00:04:31,132 --> 00:04:32,873
of all the animations connecting to it

103
00:04:32,873 --> 00:04:34,494
as a continuous motion.

104
00:04:34,494 --> 00:04:36,775
So you need to be aware of where you're coming from

105
00:04:36,775 --> 00:04:38,936
and where you're going to as you animate moves

106
00:04:38,936 --> 00:04:39,616
stemming from the idol.

107
00:04:42,191 --> 00:04:43,892
