00:22:44,873 --> 00:22:47,754
and if you have any questions about it, hit me up later.

498
00:22:47,754 --> 00:22:49,295
This was a traditional technique that they used

499
00:22:49,295 --> 00:22:51,397
in television shows back in the day

500
00:22:51,397 --> 00:22:55,299
where they had a limited number of mouth shapes.

501
00:22:55,299 --> 00:22:58,241
Basic set of 12 shapes here

502
00:22:58,241 --> 00:23:00,202
helps you quickly create organic lip sync

503
00:23:00,202 --> 00:23:02,964
without having to do a ton of cleanup at the end.

504
00:23:02,964 --> 00:23:04,925
You can use more or less than 12,

505
00:23:04,925 --> 00:23:06,686
but the basic idea is to start with 12.

506
00:23:07,834 --> 00:23:11,055
It's important to note here that these are not phonemes.

507
00:23:11,055 --> 00:23:13,075
So they're not individual shapes that are crafted

508
00:23:13,075 --> 00:23:13,876
and then plugged in.

509
00:23:13,876 --> 00:23:15,716
These shapes are built together,

510
00:23:15,716 --> 00:23:17,577
so they move in and out of each other organically.

511
00:23:17,577 --> 00:23:21,838
They feel like they're swinging from one shape to the next.

512
