635
00:28:33,795 --> 00:28:38,098
Note what is getting exported into the game.

636
00:28:38,098 --> 00:28:40,679
Not always what you see in Maya is what you export.

637
00:28:40,679 --> 00:28:45,362
Some studios use proxy rigs that drive the skeleton that gets into the game.

638
00:28:45,362 --> 00:28:47,483
Sometimes you don't see this by default.

639
00:28:47,483 --> 00:28:49,104
So make sure you check this skeleton.

640
00:28:49,104 --> 00:28:54,267
Game route, align, route, ground node, trajectory, magic box.

641
00:28:55,147 --> 00:28:58,929
It can have many names, but there is always a node that drives the character.

642
00:28:58,929 --> 00:29:00,090
It's like its parent.

643
00:29:00,090 --> 00:29:03,632
It's usually used to adjust character to the ground,

644
00:29:03,632 --> 00:29:05,573
drive collision, blends.

645
00:29:05,573 --> 00:29:07,375
Animation in this node is really important,

646
00:29:07,375 --> 00:29:09,896
and it can be the main cause of bugs.

647
00:29:09,896 --> 00:29:12,098
Avoid sudden movements with it.

648
00:29:12,098 --> 00:29:13,078
Check for smooth rotations.

649
00:29:13,078 --> 00:29:16,861
